@dev Library for managing an enumerable variant of Solidity's
 https://solidity.readthedocs.io/en/latest/types.html#mapping-types[`mapping`]
 type.
 Extension of the OpenZeppelin EnumerableMap.

@dev Adds a key-value pair to a map, or updates the value for an existing
 key. O(1).
 Returns true if the key was added to the map, that is if it was not
 already present.

@dev Removes a key-value pair from a map. O(1).
 Returns true if the key was removed from the map, that is if it was present.

typeDescriptions.typeString: function (struct EnumerableSet.Bytes32Set storage pointer,bytes32) view returns (bool)

documentation.text: @dev Returns true if the key is in the map. O(1).

typeDescriptions.typeString: function (struct EnumerableSet.Bytes32Set storage pointer) view returns (uint256)

documentation.text: @dev Returns the number of key-value pairs in the map. O(1).

typeDescriptions.typeString: function (struct EnumerableSet.Bytes32Set storage pointer,uint256) view returns (bytes32)

documentation.text:
@dev Returns the key-value pair stored at position `index` in the map. O(1).
 Note that there are no guarantees on the ordering of entries inside the
 array, and it may change when more entries are added or removed.
 Requirements:
 - `index` must be strictly less than {length}.

typeDescriptions.typeString: function (struct EnumerableMap.Map storage pointer,bytes32) view returns (bool)

documentation.text:
@dev Tries to returns the value associated with `key`.  O(1).
 Does not revert if `key` is not in the map.

typeDescriptions.typeString: function (struct EnumerableMap.Map storage pointer,bytes32) view returns (bool)
function (struct EnumerableMap.Map storage pointer,bytes32) view returns (bool)
